title: Revolution of Dignity
summary: The Revolution of Dignity (Ukrainian: Революція гідности, romanized: Revoliutsiia hidnosty), also known as the Maidan revolution[2] (Ukrainian: Українська революція 2013-2014 років, romanized: Ukrainska revoliutsiia 2013-2014 rokiv), took place in Ukraine in February 2014[2][1] at the end of the Euromaidan protests,[1] when a series of violent events involving protesters, riot police, and unknown shooters in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv culminated in the ousting of elected president Viktor Yanukovych, and the overthrow of the Ukrainian government.[1][2]
